  "ciliary_role": "Also known as Nespirin2. Colocalises with meckelin at filopodia prior to the establishment of cell polarity and ciliogenesis. Mediates centrosome migration and determi tionof centrosome/basal body positioning during early cell polarization, an essential step for ciliogenesis. It may form a linking network between the centrosome and the actin cytoskeleton (19596800). Role in nuclear migration and positioning during reti l development. Interaction partner of Pcnt in photoreceptors. Pcnt鈥揝yne-2 complex is important for ciliogenesis and outer segment formation during reti l development and for the attachment of the centrosome to the nucleus in cycling cells (30054381).",
